Package jetbrains.mps.nodeEditor.leftHighlighter

Class AbstractHighlighterPainter

  • java.lang.Object
    • jetbrains.mps.nodeEditor.leftHighlighter.AbstractHighlighterPainter
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractFoldingAreaPainter, BackgroundWithFoldingLinePainter
    public abstract class AbstractHighlighterPainter
extends Object
    Extending classes are supposed to paint appropriate UI elements in LeftEditorHighlighter (like: FoldingButtons/Brackets/VCS changes) and handle corresponding mouse events.

    All registered AbstractHighlighterPainters will be executed sequentially in an order determined by value returned form getWeight() method. Painter having less weight will be executed first.

      • getWeight

        public abstract int getWeight()
        Returns:
        weight of this AbstractPainter. All registered AbstractPainter will be painted sequentially in order determined by this value. If Painter1 need to be painted "above" Painter2 then the value returned by Painter1.getWeight() should be greater then Painter2.getWeight()
